# Frontend stack

**This file is the stack override point.** If a project deviates from any tier, edit here and note the deviation in `90-project-context.mdc`.

## Tier 1 — Foundational (installed in every project from day one)

These are always present. There is no project where styling, accessible primitives, and iconography are not needed.

| Tool | Purpose | Version rule |
|---|---|---|
| React + TypeScript (strict) | Framework + type safety | Match `.nvmrc` engine; strict mode always on |
| Tailwind CSS v4 | Utility-first styling; enforces the 8-point grid and constrained palette from `31-design.mdc` | `tailwindcss` + `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin |
| shadcn/ui | Accessible, unstyled component primitives (Radix UI underneath) | Add per-component via `npx shadcn@latest add <name>` — never hand-roll inputs, dialogs, or selects that shadcn provides |
| Lucide React | Icon set; consistent with shadcn/ui | `lucide-react` |
| Vite | Build tool and dev server | `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin; no `tailwind.config.*` needed for v4 |
| Vitest + Testing Library | Unit and component tests | Coverage via `@vitest/coverage-v8`; threshold in `vite.config.ts` |
| axe-core | Automated accessibility assertions in component tests | Use the `expectNoA11yViolations()` helper in `src/test/axe.ts` — calls axe-core directly rather than a Jest/Vitest wrapper package |

### Tailwind conventions

- No arbitrary values (e.g. `w-[137px]`) unless the value is genuinely one-off and documented with a comment.
- All colour, spacing, and typography must map to Tailwind's scale. Custom tokens go in the CSS layer via `@theme` — not inline.
- Class order is enforced by `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` at commit time.
- The `@/` alias resolves to `src/` for all imports.

### Component conventions

- Functional components with typed props. No `any` — model real types. Co-locate types with the component or in a `types.ts`.
- Compose from shadcn/ui primitives (`@/components/ui/*`). Extend them before building from scratch.
- Reference component: `src/components/Greeting.tsx` — shows Tailwind + Lucide + shadcn `Button` in a minimal example.

