## Tier 2 — Functional (standardised choice; install when the project first needs it)

The tool to reach for is decided here. Install it when the project has an actual form, API call, or server-state requirement — not before, to keep the starter scaffold minimal.

| Tool | Purpose | When to install |
|---|---|---|
| **Zod** | Runtime schema validation at every trust boundary (see `10-security-popia.mdc`) | First API response, URL param, or form payload that needs validation |
| **React Hook Form** | Performant forms with minimal re-renders; pairs with Zod via `@hookform/resolvers` | First user-input form |
| **TanStack Query** | Server-state management, caching, background refetch; replaces ad-hoc `fetch` in components | First async data dependency in a component |

Do not use alternatives to these without updating this file and documenting the reason in `90-project-context.mdc`.

---

## Tier 3 — Swappable (name a default; override per project in `90-project-context.mdc`)

These have legitimate project-specific variation. State the override and the reason in `90-project-context.mdc`.

| Category | Default | Override examples |
|---|---|---|
| Routing | React Router v7 | TanStack Router (type-safe), Next.js App Router (SSR) |
| Global state | Zustand | Jotai (fine-grained), Redux Toolkit (large teams) |
| Animation | Framer Motion (`motion`) | CSS-only, `@react-spring/web` |
| Auth | Clerk | Auth.js, Supabase Auth |
| E2E testing | Playwright | Cypress |

